**Cooldown**
================

### Overview

The cooldown is a time interval that must pass before an action can be performed again. It prevents rapid repetition of an action, such as firing a projectile or casting a spell.

### Properties

| Property | Description | Default Value |
| --- | --- | --- |
| `duration` | The length of time the cooldown lasts | 2 seconds |
| `onComplete` | A callback function to execute when the cooldown is complete | null |
| `onStart` | A callback function to execute when the cooldown starts | null |

### Example Usage

```javascript
// Create a cooldown with a duration of 5 seconds
const cooldown = new Cooldown(5000);

// Start the cooldown
cooldown.start();

// Get the remaining time on the cooldown
const remainingTime = cooldown.getRemainingTime();

// Check if the cooldown is complete
if (cooldown.isComplete()) {
  // Execute the onComplete callback function
  cooldown.onComplete();
}

// Update the cooldown every frame
